{
  "document_id": "jer-10",
  "title": "Jeremiah 10",
  "type": "scripture",
  "translation": "NRSVue",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "block_id": "jer-10-heading-idolatry-has-brought",
      "type": "heading",
      "text": "Idolatry Has Brought Ruin on Israel"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-10-1",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 1,
      "text": "Hear the word that the Lord speaks to you, O house of Israel."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-10-2",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 2,
      "text": "Thus says the Lord:"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-10-3",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 3,
      "text": "For the customs of the peoples are false:"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-10-4",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 4,
      "text": "they deck it with silver and gold;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-10-5",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 5,
      "text": "Their idols are like scarecrows in a cucumber field,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-10-6",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 6,
      "text": "There is none like you, O Lord;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-10-7",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 7,
      "text": "Who would not fear you, O King of the nations?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-10-8",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 8,
      "text": "They are both stupid and foolish;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-10-9",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 9,
      "text": "Beaten silver is brought from Tarshish"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-10-10",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 10,
      "text": "But the Lord is the true God;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-10-11",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 11,
      "text": "Thus shall you say to them: The gods who did not make the heavens and the earth shall perish from the earth and from under the heavens.,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-10-12",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 12,
      "text": "It is he who made the earth by his power,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-10-13",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 13,
      "text": "When he utters his voice, there is a tumult of waters in the heavens,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-10-14",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 14,
      "text": "Everyone is stupid and without knowledge;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-10-15",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 15,
      "text": "They are worthless, a work of delusion;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-10-16",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 16,
      "text": "The portion of Jacob is not like these,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-10-17",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 17,
      "text": "Gather up your bundle from the ground,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-10-18",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 18,
      "text": "For thus says the Lord:"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-10-19",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 19,
      "text": "Woe is me because of my hurt!"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-10-20",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 20,
      "text": "My tent is destroyed,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-10-21",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 21,
      "text": "For the shepherds are stupid"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-10-22",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 22,
      "text": "Hear, a noise! Listen, it is coming—"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-10-23",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 23,
      "text": "I know, O Lord, that the way of humans is not in their control,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-10-24",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 24,
      "text": "Correct me, O Lord, but in just measure;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jer-10-25",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 25,
      "text": "Pour out your wrath on the nations that do not know you"
    }
  ]
}